INFECTIOUS SALMON ANEMIA - CANADA (NOVA SCOTIA)
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Infectious salmon anemia - UK (Scotland) 980515225738
Infectious salmon anemia - UK (Scotland) (02) 980521185959
Infectious salmon anemia - UK (Scotland) (03) 980712104441
Infectious salmon anemia - UK (Scotland) (04) 981006165100
Infectious salmon anemia - UK (Scotland): RFI 980930125054
Date: Thursday 27 May, 1999 (1:26pm AEST)
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Australian Broadcasting Corporation - National Rural News Bulletin
(edited)

The salmon industry of Australia says it has sound reasons for wanting to
Canadian Salmon out of Australia. The salmon industry points to the news
today, which says the fish disease ISA or Infectious Salmon Anemia has been
found in Nova Scotia, Canada.
Tony Smithies, the Executive Officer of the Tasmanian Salmonid Growers
Association, says the disease has already seen the slaughter of millions of
fish in New Brunswick and Scotland, leading to substantial job losses and
government compensation pay outs.
